# Dependency cooldown — refuse to install versions published in the last 7 days.
#
# Mitigates supply-chain attacks: malicious npm versions are typically detected
# and yanked within hours-to-days. The cooldown keeps us out of the first wave.
# Lessons from Shai-Hulud worm (Nov 2025, 796 packages) and axios compromise
# (Apr 2026). Supported in pnpm 11+ and npm 11+.
#
# Own packages excluded so we don't block ourselves on internal workspace deps.
minimum-release-age=10080
minimum-release-age-exclude=@yourtechtribe-labs/*
